Shah Rukh Khan's most anticipated movie 'Raees,' which was going to clash Salman Khan starrer 'Sultan,' this Eid, has been postponed to January 26, 2017.
TNN | May 5, 2016, 12.28 PM ISTShah Rukh, Farhan Akhtar and Ritesh Sidhwani had earlier issued a joint statement which read, "It was not an easy decision to move the film.
However, a movie of such magnitude requires the appropriate showcasing and, therefore, we have decided to shift our release date to January 26, 2017."
Hrithik Roshan's 'Kaabil' to go on floors March end Actors Hrithik Roshan and Yami Gautam will start shooting for 'Kaabil' by the end of March, and will devote their time to the project till July, says the film's director Sanjay Gupta.
However, 'Raees' will now clash with Hrithik Roshan starrer 'Kaabil' and papa Rakesh Roshan is apparently not happy about this, reports Deccan Chronicle.
A source was quoted in the same report as saying, "SRK and Hrithik had met to discuss the release, but ultimately, it's the call of the makers.
Rakesh Roshan has decided to not shift the release date.
But he is very upset that Raees is also releasing on the same date.
He even called up Ritesh Sidhwani on Monday afternoon to express the same and on Tuesday when the announcement came in the newspapers, he was pretty irked.
"However, Rakesh Roshan denied having called Ritesh or being approached by SRK.
He said that he will stick to his release date, irrespective of who comes or doesn't come.Recommended By Colombia
